.SH "NAME"
Redis::Hash \- tie Perl hashes to Redis hashes
.SH "VERSION"
.IX Header "VERSION"
version 2.000
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Ties a Perl hash to Redis. Note that it doesn't use Redis Hashes, but
implements a fake hash using regular keys like \*(L"prefix:KEY\*(R".
.PP
If no \f(CW\*(C`prefix\*(C'\fR is given, it will tie the entire Redis database as a hash.
.PP
Future versions will also allow you to use real Redis hash structures.
.SH "SYNOPSYS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSYS"
.Vb 2
\&    ## Create fake hash using keys like \*(Aqhash_prefix:KEY\*(Aq
\&    tie %my_hash, \*(AqRedis::Hash\*(Aq, \*(Aqhash_prefix\*(Aq, @Redis_new_parameters;
\&
\&    ## Treat the entire Redis database as a hash
\&    tie %my_hash, \*(AqRedis::Hash\*(Aq, undef, @Redis_new_parameters;
\&
\&    $value = $my_hash{$key};
\&    $my_hash{$key} = $value;
\&
\&    @keys   = keys %my_hash;
\&    @values = values %my_hash;
\&
\&    %my_hash = reverse %my_hash;
\&
\&    %my_hash = ();
.Ve
